# Plot twilight data of a `tag`

This function display a plot of twilight time series recorded by a tag

## Usage

``` r
plot_tag_twilight(
  tag,
  twilight_line = NULL,
  transform_light = TRUE,
  twl_offset = NULL,
  plot_plotly = TRUE
)
```

## Arguments

- tag:

  a GeoPressureR `tag` object

- twilight_line:

  a twilight data.frame typically created with
  [`path2twilight()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/dev/reference/path2twilight.md)
  which is displayed as a line

- transform_light:

  logical to use a log transformation of light

- twl_offset:

  Shift of the middle of the night compared to 00:00 UTC (in hours). If
  not provided, it uses the middle of all nights.

- plot_plotly:

  logical to use `plotly`

## Value
